# Environment Variables for HelpHunt

Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in your actual values.

```env
# Supabase Configuration
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url_here
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key_here

# Admin Access (for admin panel)
NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_SECRET=your_secret_admin_key_here

# Optional: Admin Phone Number (for admin access check)
NEXT_PUBLIC_ADMIN_PHONE=+919876543210
```

## How to Get Supabase Credentials

1. Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com) and create a new project
2. Navigate to Settings > API
3. Copy the Project URL and anon/public key
4. Enable phone authentication in Authentication > Settings

## Security Notes

- Never commit `.env.local` to version control
- Use strong, unique values for admin secrets
- Rotate secrets regularly in production
